All Classes

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AddPart
    The Add Part Controller class allows the user to add parts to the parts table.
    AddProduct
    The Add Product Controller class allows the user to add products to the products table.
    AlertMessage
    The AlertMessage Controller class houses error messages and information that notify the user.
    InHouse
    The InHouse class inherits variables and methods from the Part class.
    Inventory
    The Inventory class houses the lists of parts/products and methods to manipulate them.
    Main
    This is the main class that runs the program **FUTURE ENHANCEMENT example**.
    MainScreen
    The Main Screen Controller class allows the user to view the parts/products tables, search within them, and navigate to the Add Part, Modify Part, Add Product, and Modify Product Screens.
    ModifyPart
    The Modify Part Controller class allows the user to edit a part on the parts table.
    ModifyProduct
    The Modify Product Controller class allows the user to edit a product on the products table if there are no associated parts attached.
    Outsourced
    The Outsourced class inherits variables and methods from the Part class.
    Part
    This is the provided Part class.
    Product
    This class includes a constructor, getter, and setter methods for Products.
